\subsection{Method \code{run_Preprocessing()}}{
Perform multiple different preprocessing and filtering steps on
individual raw omics datasets. Implemented steps and order can be
determined.
\subsection{Usage}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="r">}}\preformatted{Ensemble_Integration_Suite$run_Preprocessing(
  OmicsName,
  FunctionOrder = c("FeatureProp", "FilterCoverage", "FilterBlankMean",
    "FilterCorrelation", "Normalization", "NAImpute", "BatchCorrection"),
  QCName = NULL,
  BlankName = NULL,
  PooledName = NULL,
  CoverageThreshold = 0.8,
  BlankMeanMultiplier = 2,
  BlankMeanThreshold = 0.8,
  CorrelationThreshold = 0.9,
  CorMean = FALSE,
  NAMethod = NULL,
  NA_K_Neighbors = 10,
  BatchColumnName = NULL,
  PreBatchPCA = TRUE,
  BatchPCAXAxis = 1,
  BatchPCAYAxis = 2
)}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

\subsection{Arguments}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="arguments">}}
\describe{
\item{\code{OmicsName}}{Name of omics type.}

\item{\code{FunctionOrder}}{Character vector with any of the following 7 steps
in any order.
\itemize{
\item \code{"FeatureProp"}: Calculate the feature proportion of feature total
per sample.
\item \code{"FilterCoverage"}: Filter features based on NA proportion across
samples, by user defined threshold.
\item \code{"FilterBlankMean"}: Filter features based on its measurement in
blank samples. Multiply the mean feature measurement of the blank
samples by a user defined multiplier, and filter the features in which
less than the user defined threshold exceed the multiplied blank mean.
Only possible if blank samples are available.
\item \code{"FilterCorrelation"}: Filter out correlated features. Calculate
pairwise correlations between features, and filter out the features
with correlation above the user defined threshold. One feature per
correlated group is kept in the dataset. The features which are
filtered out are stored in a list at
$Preprocessed_Omics$Correlated_Features.
\item \code{"Normalization"}: Feature Z-score normalization.
\item \code{"NAImpute"}: NA imputation or replacement with one of the following
methods: KNN imputation, missForest, zero replacement, omit NA.
\item \code{"BatchCorrection"}: Correct for batch effect using ComBat. Only
possible if batch information is available for samples.
}}

\item{\code{QCName}}{Common string in the name of quality control samples.}

\item{\code{BlankName}}{Common string in the name of blank samples.}

\item{\code{PooledName}}{Common string in the name of pooled samples.}

\item{\code{CoverageThreshold}}{Numerical threshold for feature coverage
filtering performed in \code{"FilterCoverage"}. Default is 0.8 (at least 0.8
of the samples do not have NAs in a feature).}

\item{\code{BlankMeanMultiplier}}{Numerical by which blank feature mean is
multiplied in \code{"FilterBlankMean"}. Default is 2.}

\item{\code{BlankMeanThreshold}}{Numerical threshold for blank mean filtering
performed in \code{"FilterBlankMean"}. Default is 0.8 (at least 0.8 of the
samples are larger than blank feature mean * BlankMeanMultiplier).}

\item{\code{CorrelationThreshold}}{Numerical threshold for correlation filtering
performed in \code{"FilterCorrelation"}. Default is 0.9 (if pairwise
correlation between two features is 0.9 or larger, one of the features is
removed).}

\item{\code{CorMean}}{Whether to calculate the mean measurements for the
correlated features. If \code{FALSE} (default), a representative feature from
the correlated group of features is kept in the dataset. If \code{TRUE}, the
mean of all feature measurements for a group of correlated features is
included in the dataset.}

\item{\code{NAMethod}}{String with method for \code{"NAImpute"}: \code{"KNN"},
\code{"missForest"}, \code{"zero replacement"} or \code{"omit NA"}.}

\item{\code{NA_K_Neighbors}}{Numerical for the number of K nearest neighbors
when using \code{"NAMethod"} \code{"KNN"}. Default is 10.}

\item{\code{BatchColumnName}}{String of the column name which contains batching
information in the metadata file.}

\item{\code{PreBatchPCA}}{Whether to create a PCA plot of the sample data prior
to batch effect correction. If \code{TRUE} (default), a PCA plot of the
samples before batch effect correction will be created and printed.}

\item{\code{BatchPCAXAxis}}{Numerical to indicate which principle component will
be used for X axis in the PCA plot. Default is 1.}

\item{\code{BatchPCAYAxis}}{Numerical to indicate which principle component will
be used for Y axis in the PCA plot. Default is 2.}
}
\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}
}
