Perform multi-omics integration using multiple co-inertia analysis
(MCIA) from the omicade4 package.
\subsection{Usage}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="r">}}\preformatted{Ensemble_Integration_Suite$run_MCIA(
  PerformCluster = TRUE,
  Clusters = NULL,
  Components = NULL,
  SVD = TRUE
)}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

\subsection{Arguments}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="arguments">}}
\describe{
\item{\code{PerformCluster}}{Whether to perform k-means clustering on the sample
embeddings. Default is \code{TRUE}.}

\item{\code{Clusters}}{The number of sample clusters to be created. Can be a
single integer to calculate a single cluster assignment, or a range to
calculate multiple cluster assignments.}

\item{\code{Components}}{The number of components to reduce the data to. Needs
to be a single integer.}

\item{\code{SVD}}{Whether singular value decomposition should be used. Default
is \code{TRUE}.}
}
\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}
}
